0. Prologue

Everything begins in freefall.

Ideas, failures, metaphors, doubts, drafts, instincts, fears, sparks ‚Äî
all tumbling through cognitive space with no clear destination.

Most systems try to catch the stones before they fall.
Pantheon-Prime takes the opposite approach:

Let them fall together.

Because when enough falling stones share the same gravity,
they do not shatter.

They interlock.

And the collapse becomes a structure.

